Henry Albert Reed (17 May 1892 – 3 May 1963) was an English cricketer. Reed's batting style is unknown. He was born at Bristol.
Reed made his first-class debut for Gloucestershire against Essex in 1921 County Championship. He made five further first-class appearances for the county, the last of which came against Essex in the 1923 County Championship. In his six first-class matches for Gloucestershire, he scored a total of 110 runs at an average of 9.16, with a high score of 45.He died at Redland, Bristol, on 3 May 1963.
